The next morning, after a 10.5 hour journey, I was shaken along noisy rails with a rhythm reminiscent of the old world of the famous documentary The Night Mail, and finally arrived in the Turkish capital - presented as a new city of a new secular state, turning its back on its German past.
But the AKP with its well-known Islamist roots, represents an example of a change in the Turkish consensus.
He suspected the West, and Washington in particular.
