That in Quebec, as in Canada, we have no real laws to actually preserve our heritage?
Did you know that the French government is spending three and a half million euros to restore the only Chinon castle in the Loire Valley?
In our American neighbors, it is written in their country's constitution that the protection of heritage is part of American culture and that this heritage must be protected by all citizens, all elected officials and all government departments, and that in concert.
